OL,3,CMan who had life saved by
OL,4,Cdefibrillator urges people to maintain
OL,5,Cthem
OL,7,FA man from Guernsey who had his life
OL,8,Fsaved by the fast actions of those
OL,9,Faround him using a defibrillator is
OL,10,Fcalling on people to come forward and
OL,11,Fhelp maintain the island's network of
OL,12,Fdevices.
OL,14,FRick Denton is a 'guardian' which
OL,15,Fmeans he now helps to maintain and
OL,16,Fcheck the equipment regularly after it
OL,17,Fhelped him during a cardiac arrest.
OL,19,FHe was having a coffee at Les Cotlis
OL,20,Fwhen he collapsed and does not
OL,21,Fremember much of what happened.
