OL,3,CMan who had life saved by
OL,4,Cdefibrillator urges people to maintain
OL,5,Cthem
OL,7,F"To have somebody who's very badly
OL,8,Fdamaged because nobody resuscitated
OL,9,Fthem soon enough is horrendous,
OL,10,Fwhereas we have four people on our
OL,11,Fcommittee who are back doing very high-
OL,12,Fflying jobs because somebody actually
OL,13,Facted immediately."
OL,15,FRick explains: "It's not just about
OL,16,Fage or fitness, it's really about the
OL,17,Fheart itself and its mechanisms so we
OL,18,Fhave to be prepared."
